The Chronicle Fungai Muderere, Senior Sports Reporter
THE draw for the Bulawayo Province Pool Association (BPPA) two-day Easter tournament will be held this evening at Masters Pool Centre. The tournament that will be played tomorrow and Easter Saturday will feature BPPA Premier League clubs, and group stage matches will be played at Skittle Inn, Nokkies Sports Bar, Dawn Sports Bar and Basement Sports Bar. New joint Chillers Sports Bar located in Nkulumane will host the finals.  The 5×5 AAPA format with two substitutes, race to 13 will be used in the contest. Eventual winners of the two-day event will take home US$400 and the first runners-up will pocket US$200. Third and fourth place finishers will receive US$150 and US$100 respectively. Registration closes today and the fee is pegged at US$50. — @FungaiMuderere